-- 
Saudi Arabia Creates Ministry of Housing, SPA Reports

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-03-26T07:50:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-26/saudi-arabia-creates-ministry-of-housing-spa-reports.html
Saudi Arabia  created a ministry for
housing and named Shuwaish al-Duwaihi, the director of the
General Housing Authority, as minister, the  Saudi Press Agency 
reported yesterday, citing a royal decree.  The new ministry will assume all duties and
responsibilities of the state-run housing agency, SPA said. On
March 18, King Abdullah Bin Abdulaziz ordered the spending of
250 billion riyals ($67 billion) to build 500,000 housing units.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
